DockZ has no external Swift dependencies. All application code is original or
uses Apple system frameworks.

Guest disk images that DockZ builds bundle separately-licensed upstream
software (Alpine Linux, Debian, Ubuntu, Docker Engine, k3s, kubeadm, etc.).
Those components retain their own respective licenses and are not covered by
this Work's license.

DockZ does not redistribute the Docker CLI. When a Mac has no `docker` binary,
DockZ can download the official static builds at the user's request:

  - Docker CLI      https://download.docker.com/mac/static/stable/aarch64/
                    (Docker Inc., Apache License 2.0)
  - Compose plugin  https://github.com/docker/compose/releases
                    (Docker Inc., Apache License 2.0)

They are fetched over HTTPS, verified against pinned SHA-256 digests, stored in
the user's DockZ data folder, and retain their own upstream licenses.
